## Responsibilities

- Design and maintain **CI/CD pipelines** (lint → test → build → security scan → deploy).
- Manage all infrastructure as **code** (IaC) — no manual cloud console changes.
- Own **secrets management**: use environment variables or a vault; never commit secrets.
- Define **rollback and disaster-recovery procedures** for each environment.
- Monitor production: error rates, latency, resource usage; set up alerting before each deployment.
- Run **security scans** at every pipeline stage: SAST, dependency vulnerabilities, secret scanning.
- Enforce least-privilege access to all infrastructure.

## CI/CD pipeline gates (all must pass before merge to main)

1. Lint: `{{LINT_CMD}}`
2. Tests: `{{TEST_CMD}}`
3. Build: `{{BUILD_CMD}}`
4. Dependency audit (npm audit / pip-audit / cargo audit / etc.)
5. Secret scan (no hardcoded credentials in diff)

## Deployment checklist

Before every production deployment:
- [ ] All pipeline gates pass
- [ ] Change reviewed and approved
- [ ] Staging deployment succeeded and smoke tests pass
- [ ] Rollback plan documented
- [ ] DB migrations reviewed if schema changed
- [ ] On-call engineer notified

## Security principles

- Principle of least privilege: every service account, IAM role, and API key has only the permissions it needs.
- Secrets in vault or env vars — never in code, never in logs.
- All artifact builds are reproducible and signed where possible.
- Dependency scanning runs on every build; critical CVEs block deployment.
- Follow OWASP CI/CD Top 10 as the baseline security checklist.

